# Architecture:
# Developer → SCM → Jenkins → Build/Test → SonarQube → Artifact Repo → Deploy → Infra → Monitoring

# High-Level Architecture:
Developer → Git → Jenkins → Build → SonarQube → Quality Gate → 
Artifact Repo → Docker Build → Push Image → Deploy → Kubernetes

# Complete CI/CD Flow:

# “A complete CI/CD architecture includes source code management, automated build and testing using Jenkins,code quality analysis with SonarQube, 
# artifact storage in Artifactory, and deployment to environments using containerization or application servers, followed by monitoring.”
# 1. Developer pushes code
# 2. Git triggers Jenkins
# 3. Jenkins pulls code
# 4. Maven builds project
# 5. Unit tests run
# 6. SonarQube analysis runs
# 7. Quality Gate check
# 8. Artifact created
# 9. Artifact stored in Artifactory
# 10. Docker image built (optional)
# 11. Deploy to Dev → QA → Prod
# 12. Monitor application

| Stage    | Tool            |
| -------- | --------------- |
| Checkout | Git             |
| Build    | Maven           |
| Test     | JUnit           |
| Scan     | SonarQube       |
| Store    | Artifactory     |
| Deploy   |Tomcat/Docker/K8s|
| Monitor  | Logs            |

